Class LoginDialog

  • java.lang.Object

              • gui.dialog.LoginDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants

    public class LoginDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog
    Extension of the JDialog class. It is used for logging into the application. Contains a username and a password field. If the user does not have an account yet, he or she can choose to create one.
    Author:
    Borko Arsovic, Milan Radeta
    See Also:
    SignUpDialog, Serialized Form
